==English==

===Alternative forms===
* {{l|en|sow the wind and reap the whirlwind}}
* {{l|en|reap the whirlwind}}

===Etymology===
A reference to [[w:Book of Hosea|Hosea]] [[s:Bible (King James)/Hosea#Chapter 8|8:7]]: "they have sown the wind, and they shall reap the whirlwind"

===Proverb===
{{head|en|proverb}}

# Every [[decision]] has [[consequence]]s; a [[person]]'s [[action]]s will [[come back]] to them; if one starts [[trouble]] or [[take action|takes actions]] in spite of the [[discontent]] they cause, one will [[incur]] [[negative]] consequences.

====Synonyms====
* {{l|en|what goes around comes around}}
* {{l|en|reap what you sow}}
*like karma  see Hindu oldest source  

